==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bridoon
<hw>Bri*doon"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>bridon</ets>, from <ets>bride</ets>; of German origin. See
<er>Bridle</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The snaffle
and rein of a military bridle, which acts independently of the bit, at
the pleasure of the rider. It is used in connection with a curb bit,
which has its own rein.</def> <rj><au>Campbell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brie</ent>⟦br⟧
